The paper deals with the complexity of piecewise testable languages, which are a topic in formal language theory (FL). The main result concerns the separability of regular languages, which is a topic in computational complexity (CC). The paper also involves the use of complexity classes such as PSpace and PTime, which are topics in computational complexity (CC) and complexity theory (DS). Finally, the paper involves the use of automata theory (IT) and logic (LO) in its proofs.
